-- Canada Gets Names of 1,800 HSBC Swiss Account Owners, Globe & Mail Reports
-- B y   J a m e s   K r a u s
-- 2010-09-30T08:41:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-30/canada-gets-names-of-1-800-hsbc-swiss-account-owners-globe-says.html
Canadian tax authorities have
received details on almost 1,800 accounts at the Swiss unit of
HSBC Plc, the Globe and Mail reported, citing a spokesman for
the Minister of National Revenue.  The accounts, which were submitted to Canada by the French
government, are among those disclosed by former HSBC employee
Herve Falciani, the newspaper said.  About 1,600 of the HSBC accounts turned over to the French
had U.S. owners, the Globe said.     Canadian residents can hold accounts overseas provided they
detail their worldwide income, the newspaper added.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
